==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presentable
<hw>Pre*sent"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sentable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable or
admitting of being presented; suitable to be exhibited, represented, or
offered; fit to be brought forward or set forth; hence, fitted to be
introduced to another, or to go into society; <as>as, ideas that are
<ex>presentable</ex> in simple language; she is not <ex>presentable</ex>
in such a gown.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Admitting of the presentation of a clergiman;
<as>as, a church <ex>presentable</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presentaneous</ent>⟦br⟧
